\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Notice that when you type in underlay, Calliope does not immediately move the staff below the underlay down to make room for the underlay.  You need to use one of the formatting commands (such as \fs24\f1\b0\i0 R\f1 eset Page\f0  or the \fs24\f1\b0\i0 A\f1 djust\f0  commands).  Most of the time the default amount of room required for underlay is adequante.  However, in certain circumstances it is useful to override it.  Here is a situation where Calliope has allowed enough space between staves to allow for underlay, but because not all staves have underlay, the separation of staves is unequal:\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qc\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic4 graphic_6.eps \width7580\height3940
