\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Sometimes unequal separation is needed, particularly in large scores, but here it does not look right.  The answer is to override the default setting by specifying `Expand enough for equal spacing'.  To do this, call up the System Inspector by command-clicking the system marker (the highlighted square marker at the upper right-hand corner of the system.  \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qc\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic4 graphic_1.eps \width5980\height6900
}¬} \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Notice that the Expand to Amount field becomes disabled.  Calliope will automatically expand the system to the minimum amount necessary to produce equidistant spacing of staves.   The system appears reformatted as follows:\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qc\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic4 graphic_4.eps \width7720\height4180
