\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 A subsequent lesson will show how to input the multiple voice notation seen on the second staff.  For the moment don't attempt to reproduce this example.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The system is automatically formatted so that the upper underlay just clears both the top-staff underlay and the note stems, but collides with the slur marks, which are not taken into consideration by the adjustment algorithm.  Here is an example in which the default has been overridden in two ways:\par
