\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb240\sa0\li0\ri0\f1\fs28\b0\i1\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 How it works\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Calliope automatically lays out staves to accommodate the material above the staff ± bar numbers, staff headings and verses above notes ± so that these do not clash with the staff above.  However, in some cases such as the one illustrated above, to improve the quality of layout it is necessary to guarantee an amount of space beyond that which Calliope will automatically provide.  This `guaranteed minimum amount' is what the \fs24\f1\b0\i0 T\f1 op Margin\f0  figure is.  This is why a small default value of 3 or 4 makes sense.  For example, if Calliope determines that the amount of clearance required above the staff is \i X\i0  (in ss units), then the actual top margin to be used is whatever is the maximum of \i X\i0  and the top margin value.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 In yet other situations, it is desirable to interpret the top margin not as a guaranteed minimum, but as a fixed amount which is not influenced by whatever other material may appear on the staff.  Setting the \fs24\f1\b0\i0 F\f1 ixed\f0  switch will accomplish this, and the specified top margin will be used regardless of other considerations.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Similarly, the Underlay Offsets are guaranteed minimums.  Calliope will automatically compute the baseline for underlay so that it does not clash with notes.  However, in some situations, for example underlay clashing with punctuation that can legitimately intrude into the underlay area,  is it desirable to offset by more than the calculated amount.\par
